                    "description": "\u2022 Facilitating the Executive Board in their strategic internal and external communications;\n\u2022 Protecting and enhancing the corporate story and brand identity internally;\n\u2022 Partnering with various global internal functions to develop and deploy compelling communication programs (including Strategy, Finance, and HR);\n\u2022 Managing a team of Corporate Communications professionals;\n\u2022 Reporting to the Global Corporate Communications Director;\n\n\nPon \u2013 one of the Netherlands\u2019 biggest family businesses \u2013 is a leading global company with nearly 14,000 employees operating in 33 countries. From cars and bikes to marine engines and electrical technology: we know the drill. We operate in four different business clusters. \n\nOur Automotive cluster focuses on the import, logistics, marketing, distribution, service and maintenance of the brands Volkswagen, Audi, Porsche, SEAT, \u0160KODA and the luxury brands Bugatti, Bentley and Lamborghini. In addition, we also the import and distribute MAN trucks, buses and Volkswagen light commercial vehicles. We are geographically active in Europe and the United States. \n\nOur Bike cluster consists of premium brand portfolio of more than 10 bicycle brands. The group has locations in the Netherlands, Germany, the United States, Canada, China, Taiwan, and Australia. In 2018 some 800,000 Pon bikes will make their way to customers around the world. \n\nOur Equipment en Power Systems cluster consists of the official Caterpillar dealership in the Netherlands, Norway, Greenland, Sweden and Denmark. In addition, we have a joint-venture in Brazil and Vietnam. We supply total solutions with Cat machines, engines and generators. \n\nOur Industrial Mobility cluster supplies technical services and flow control solutions for the marine, nickel, and oil & gas industry in the United States, Asia and Australia. We supply valves, actuators, control and fire safety systems, as well as material handling solutions, such as forklifts in these various industries.",
